<page>
    <topic>Button style</topic>
    <description>The Button style property specifies the style of the buttons.</description>
   <sections>
<section>
    
    <description>Options for button style include:</description>
    <cases>
        <case>
            <figure><title>Text only</title><link>images/textonly.png</link></figure>
        </case>
         <case>
            <figure><title>Image only</title><link>images/imageonly.png</link></figure>
        </case>
         <case>
         
             <figure><title>Text followed by image</title><link>images/textfbimage.png</link></figure>
        </case>
         <case>
        
              <figure><title>Image followed by text</title><link>images/imagefbtext.png</link></figure>
        </case>
         <case>
          
              <figure><title>Image above text</title><link>images/imageabovetext.png</link></figure>
        </case>
         <case>
              <figure><title>Text above image</title><link>images/textaboveimage.png</link></figure>
        </case>
       
    </cases>
    <note>With the "text followed by image" and "image followed by text" examples, setting the text Alignment right or left justified the icons</note>
</section>    
<section>
    <description>The choice of button style has some impact the Data Series Mapping options for the control.
    </description>
</section>   
       
   </sections>
</page>